def: Of or pertaining to delusions; as, delusional monomania.
To awaken from a trance or an enchantment. Hudibras.
An idol; a puppet; a doll. [Obs.] Selden. Shak.
Full of beauty; beautiful; very handsome. [Mostly poetic] --Beau"te*ous*ly, adv. --
With a cheerful spirit; in a cheerful or good-tempered manner.
The small arch or bar at right angles to the strings of aviolin, guitar, etc., serving of raise them and transmit theirvibrations to the body of the instrument.
Entering into covenant; contracting; as, contrahent parties.[Obs.] Mede.
A large North American snipe (Symphemia semipalmata); -- calledalso pill-willet, will-willet, semipalmated tattler, or snipe, ducksnipe, and stone curlew. Carolina willet, the Hudsonian godwit.
Without a base; having no foundation or support. "The baselessfabric of this vision." Shak.
